    <item>
      <title>Farewell - From Ashes ..</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Stormhammer&amp;message.id=2004#M2004</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font face="Comic Sans MS"&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;After receiving a number of requests from people for an explanation as to why I (Ashes) left Stormhammer in the manner I did, I have given the matter some thought and have decided to explain my reasons to you all.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Many of you will no doubt remember the GM run *event* in the Overthere a week or two ago. The event in itself was a fun one, but what happened at the end left a *lot* of people feeling angry. The GM in charge of that particular event was Deodan, and we were asked to random 2000 on a Shield of the Planar Assassin, a quite magnificent shield indeed - the highest roll would win. Well, I nearly fell off of my chair when I actually *won* the item - but, in a quite astonishing manner the GM refused to hand me my reward because someone had pointed out to him that I was not level 70. Well, fair enough, or was it? In my opinion no, because we weren’t told beforehand that one had to be level 70 in order to receive the shield. Many, many people argued on my behalf, and one person (Abyssmal) was actually removed from the zone for his protests. As soon as I was told I was not to get my reward, I simply left the zone, and sat alone in Steamfont Mountains. For well over an hour I had tell after tell after tell letting me know that everyone thought I had been treated badly.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;I try never to do things in the heat of the moment, so slept on the matter - and the following morning I felt so annoyed that I decided to write a protest to the GM. I mentioned in my letter that I genuinely felt that GM Deodan had not been fair, and that if the matter was not *put right* I would not attend any further events - furthermore, I would not be attending any Agency runs either. Xurdaben had asked us all to Email him of any target we would like to have a shot at - so I asked for a trip to the PoSky in the hope of perhaps getting my Necromancer 1.0 epic completed. In the Email to Deodan I asked that any trip to the PoSky on my behalf be ignored.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;GM Deodan did reply to me - we had a long chat about the matter, and he was rather courteous in telling me that he had made a genuine error by not announcing that one had to be level 70 to roll. Okay - well, my reply was to tell him that in *my* opinion the shield should *never* have been offered as a reward at a level 55+ event - after all, not *everyone* was level 70. Between us, we agreed that the shield should not have been set as a reward.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;I don’t *want* to be level 70 - I play in the style that *I* want to - I pay my&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;own fee and am more than entitled to farm AA points rather than level if I so wish. Heck, I stayed in the Plane of Nightmare for a whole year and made 256 AA points when I was level 56! I only levelled to 65 so that I could enter Time!&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Anyway, due to overwhelming requests to turn up for the events from my friends on Stormhammer, I tried to put the matter behind me and see out the last two weeks of *fun* - but I knew for sure that if any further wrongdoings were to happen then I’d leave the server.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;A few days ago there was another event, again, run by GM Deodan which saw us all running around looking for rare items that drop from Dragons! Three Dragons were killed, and the reward was to be the chance of rolling on an Ogre Illusion Cape - whose name escapes me at this moment in time.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;The event ended and I’m so sorry to say that once again the rules set by GM Deodan were extraordinarily unfair - heavily favouring those that were level 70. In fact, if I recall correctly a level 70 had no fewer than *three* chances to win one of these items, yet anyone that was under level 70 only had one chance - again, to me this is was most unfair! I made my feelings known in the raid channel, and refused to roll on anything. The event was marked on the Legends calendar as being for level 51+, so I think it only fair that *everyone* that was 51+ and had attended should be given the same *three* chances there and then. I gated away, and once again I left my PC with a feeling of wrongdoings by GM Deodan. Again I slept on the matter, and the following morning I mentioned to my good friends Scientia and Aceso that I felt that I would not be able to stay on the server attending events when there is such an obvious bias towards those that chose to level to 70.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;I took a few more hours at the request of my friends to reconsider, but honestly, I did not want to continue to go to the remaining events only to be left feeling upset at the end of them. When GM Lydrea came on duty I asked her to contact me and I then asked her to move Ashes away from Stormhammer. GM Lydrea was totally wonderful to me, and asked me to stay, but I had to be true to my own word - so less than five minutes later Ashes was moved to Firiona Vie and my other suite of characters, including Chinqua the Wizard, who many old-timers to Stormhammer will no doubt remember were move logged to Maelin.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;I had been a member of the Stormhammer community since the very first day - and had made many, many friends during my four years there. I gave Xurdaben an Amulet of Necropotance and a pre-nerf Circlet of Shadows as my gifts to you all - these items were *meant* to be rolled on at an Agency event, but so far as I’m aware these items have not been offered to you - so if you happen to read this please DO remind Xurdaben to offer these items to you all to roll on.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;It just remains for me to say my thank you to several people here - Firstly to GM Lydrea for being so wonderful and for looking after us all. Xurdaben and Night Wing for their efforts in seeing that we managed to gain access to Time - and conquering the all fearsome Quarm - without cheese I might add!&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;I’d like that thank Piebelly for helping me so very often, Tharkis for all the punts, it won’t be the same with out you bud. Scientia and Vexx too, I’ll miss you both. Fanta, yes, you and I had a few serious and rather heated exchanges of words from time-to-time, but thank you *very* much for all that you gave to the Stormhammer community by way of raid-leading and the *numerous* items you freely gave away. Giantt, simply the best raid leader I’ve ever had the honour of working under. Turaar, you were fabulous too, I hope you manage to make that *perfect* Ranger one day. Lepracon, stay in touch neighbour! Kazdrina - without doubt, you *do* have the very *best* milkshakes! /wink ..&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Lastly but by no means least, I’d like to thank Synthesis for allowing me to be part of the family.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Farewell my friends - and thank you *so* much for the memories!&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Ashes, Stormhammer Necromancer - proud of *not* being level 70!&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p align="justify"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Fri, 17 Feb 2006 06:37:33 GMT</pubDate>
