    <item>
      <title>Closed Legends Account Surprise / Lessons Learned</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Stormhammer&amp;message.id=1959#M1959</link>
      <description>Tuesday I went to log into Everquest, and much to my surprise I found that my account status was "Closed".  This was not a problem with the credit card, as they don't refuse charges like that.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;What had happened is that the end of the billing cycle had arrived, and because they were no longer charging the Legends fee, they insted closed the account.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;What you have to do to resolve this (many thanks to Naladini!) is go to the account page and re-sign up including your credit card information.  The Legends option won't be available, but just sign up for the regular service or whatever options you want.  You can still log onto stormhammer, and all of your characters are still there (at least mine were).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;So as your billing dates hit, you may find that your account will "auto-close" much to your surprise.  Even better, you will find there is no way to post to this very board to ask for help, because your station login is GONE!  &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;And, if you are very lucky it can happen when SOE support is gone for the week, and you can be left stumped unless someone kind helps you out.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Vexx</description>
      <pubDate>Fri, 30 Dec 2005 15:54:06 GMT</pubDate>
